obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (31828)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31828&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Compensatory`
  line `Afforestation Fund Act, 2016.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India except the State of Jammu and Kashmir*.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, it shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 30th September, 2018, vide notification NO. S.O. 3967(E), dated 13th August, 2018, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (31829)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31829&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "ad hoc Authority" means the ad hoc Compensatory Afforestation Fund Management and`
  line `Planning Authority constituted under the order dated the 5th May, 2006 of the Supreme Court in T.N.`
  line `Godavarman Thirumulpad vs. Union of India and Others, [Writ Petition (Civil) No. 202 of 1995];`
  line
  line `(b) "Chairperson, National Authority" means the Chairperson of the governing body of the`
  line `National Authority;`
  line
  line `(c) "Chairperson, State Authority" means the Chairperson of the governing body of the State`
  line Authority;
  line
  line `(d) "compensatory afforestation" means afforestation done in lieu of the diversion of forest land`
  line `for non-forestry use under the Forest (Conservation) Act, 1980 (69 of 1980);`
  line
  line `(e) "environmental services" includes—`
  line
  line `(i) provision of goods such as wood, non-timber forest products, fuel, fodder, water and`
  line `provision of services such as grazing, tourism, wildlife protection and life support;`
  line
  line `(ii) regulating services such as flood moderation, carbon sequestration and health of soil, air`
  line `and water regimes;`
  line
  line `(iii) supporting such other services necessary for the production of ecosystem services,`
  line `biodiversity, nutrient cycling and primary production including pollination and seed dispersal;`
  line
  line `(f) "Head of the regional office" means the senior-most officer appointed by the Central`
  line `Government at regional office to deal with the forest conservation matters under the Forest`
  line `(Conservation) Act, 1980 (69 of 1980);`
  line
  line `(g) "monitoring group" means a group of experts to monitor the activities undertaken from`
  line `amounts released from the National Fund and State Fund constituted under sub-section (3) of section`
  line 9;
  line
  line `(h) "National Authority" means National Compensatory Afforestation Fund Management and`
  line `Planning Authority constituted under section 8;`
  line
  line `(i) "National Fund" means the National Compensatory Afforestation Fund established under subsection (1) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(j) "net present value" means the quantification of the environmental services provided for the`
  line `forest area diverted for non-forestry uses, as may be determined by an expert committee appointed by`
  line `the Central Government from time to time in this regard;`
  line
  line `(k) "penal compensatory afforestation" means afforestation work to be undertaken over and above`
  line `the compensatory afforestation specified in the guidelines issued under the Forest (Conservation) Act,`
  line `1980, in lieu of the extent of area over which non-forestry activities have been carried out without`
  line `obtaining prior approval of the competent authority under the Forest (Conservation) Act, 1980 (69 of`
  line `1980);`
  line
  line `(l) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made by the Central Government in consultation with`
  line `the State Governments under this Act;`
  line
  line `(m) "State Authority" means the State Compensatory Afforestation Fund Management and`
  line `Planning Authority constituted under section 10;`
  line
  line `(n) "State Fund" means the State Compensatory Afforestation Fund established by each State`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(o) "State Government" includes Union territory Administration;`
  line
  line `(p) "user agency" means any person, organisation or company or department of the Central`
  line `Government or State Government making a request for diversion or de-notification of forest land for`
  line `non-forest purpose or using forest land for non-forest purpose in accordance with the provisions`
  line `contained in the Forest (Conservation) Act, 1980 (69 of 1980) and the rules made and guidelines issued, thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (31830)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of National Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31830&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf, there shall be established for the`
  line `purposes of this Act, a special Fund to be called the "National Compensatory Afforestation Fund" under`
  line `the public account of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The National Fund shall be under the control of the Central Government and managed by the`
  line `National Authority in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) On the date of establishment of the National Fund, all monies collected by the State Governments`
  line `and Union territory Administrations which has been placed under the ad hoc Authority and deposited in`
  line `the nationalised banks shall be transferred to the National Fund.`
  line
  line `(4) There shall also be credited into the National Fund, by each State on yearly basis, ten per cent. of`
  line `the funds realised from the user agencies in respect of the forest land diverted in their favour, which have`
  line `been credited directly into the State Fund.`
  line
  line `(5) There shall also be credited to the National Fund—`
  line
  line `(a) grants-in-aid received, if any, by the National Authority;`
  line
  line `(b) any loan taken or any borrowings made by the National Authority;`
  line
  line `(c) any other sums received by the National Authority by way of benefaction, gift or donations.`
  line
  line `(6) The monies received in the National Fund shall be an interest bearing fund under public accounts`
  line `of India.`
  line
  line `(7) The balance in the National Fund shall be non-lapsable and get interest as per the rate declared by`
  line `the Central Government on year to year basis.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (31831)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Establishment of State Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31831&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as each State Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf, there shall be established for the purposes of`
  line `this Act, a special Fund to be called the "State Compensatory Afforestation Fund-......... (name`
  line `of State)" under public accounts of such State:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of Union territory having no legislature, such fund shall be established under the`
  line `public account of Union of India with effect from such date as the Union territory Administration may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Fund in each State shall be under the control of the State Government of such State and`
  line `managed by the State Authority of such State, in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) There shall be credited into the State Fund of a State—`
  line
  line `(i) the unspent balance of all monies which has been transferred by ad hoc Authority to the State`
  line `Compensatory Afforestation Compensatory Afforestation Funds Management and Planning Authority`
  line `constituted in such State in compliance of guidelines dated the 2nd July, 2009;`
  line
  line `(ii) all monies transferable from the National Fund under clause (a) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(iii) all monies realised from user agencies by such State towards compensatory afforestation,`
  line `additional compensatory afforestation, penal compensatory afforestation, net present value, catchment`
  line `area treatment plan or any money for compliance of conditions stipulated by the Central Government`
  line `while according approval under the provisions of the Forest (Conservation) Act, 1980 (69 of 1980);`
  line and
  line
  line `(iv) the funds recoverable from user agencies by such State in cases where forest land diverted`
  line `falls within the protected areas, that is, areas notified under sections 18, 26A or 35 of the Wild Life`
  line `(Protection) Act, 1972 (53 of 1972) for undertaking activities relating to the protection of biodiversity`
  line `and wildlife.`
  line
  line `(4) A State Government may also credit to the State Fund constituted by it—`
  line
  line `(i) grants-in-aid received, if any, by the State Authority;`
  line
  line `(ii) any loan taken or any borrowings made by the State Authority;`
  line
  line `(iii) any other sums received by the State Authority by way of benefaction, gift or donations.`
  line
  line `(5) The monies received in the State Fund shall be an interest bearing fund under public accounts.`
  line
  line `(6) The balance in each State Fund shall be non-lapsable and get interest as per the rate declared by`
  line `the Central Government on year to year basis.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (31832)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Disbursement and utilisation of National Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31832&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the`
  line `monies available in the National Fund shall be disbursed and utilised in the following manner, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) ninety per cent. of the all monies collected by a State, which has been placed under the ad`
  line `hoc Authority and the interest accrued thereon, shall be transferred to the State Fund established in`
  line `such state under sub-section (1) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the balance ten per cent. of all monies collected by the States and Union territory`
  line `Administrations, which has been placed under the ad hoc Authority and the interest accrued thereon,`
  line `and all fresh accrual to the National Fund, as provided in sub-section (4) of section 3, and the interest`
  line `accrued thereon, shall be utilised for meeting—`
  line
  line `(i) the non-recurring and recurring expenditure for the management of the National Authority`
  line `including the salary and allowances payable to its officers and other employees;`
  line
  line `(ii) the expenditure incurred on monitoring and evaluation of works executed by the National`
  line `Authority and each State Authority;`
  line
  line `(iii) the expenditure incurred on specific schemes approved by governing body of the`
  line `National Authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, "scheme" includes any institute, society, centre of`
  line `excellence in the field of forest and wildlife, pilot schemes, standardisation of codes and guidelines and`
  line `such other related activities for the forestry and wildlife sector.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (31833)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Disbursement and utilisation of State Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31833&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the monies`
  line `available in a State Fund shall be disbursed and utilised in the following manner, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the money received for compensatory afforestation, additional compensatory afforestation,`
  line `penal compensatory afforestation, catchment area treatment plan and for any other site specific`
  line `scheme may be used as per site-specific schemes submitted by the State along with the approved`
  line `proposals for diversion of forest land under the Forest (Conservation) Act, 1980 (69 of 1980);`
  line
  line `(b) the monies received towards net present value and penal net present value shall be used for`
  line `artificial regeneration (plantation), assisted natural regeneration, forest management, forest protection,`
  line `forest and wildlife related infrastructure development, wildlife protection and management, supply of`
  line `wood and other forest produce saving devices and other allied activities in the manner as may be`
  line prescribed;
  line
  line `(c) the interest accrued on funds available in a State Fund and the interest accrued on all monies`
  line `collected by the State Governments, which has been placed under the ad hoc Authority and deposited`
  line `in the nationalised banks, in compliance of the directions of the Supreme Court dated the 5th May,`
  line `2006, shall be used for conservation and development of forest and wildlife in the manner as may be`
  line prescribed;
  line
  line `(d) all monies realised from the user agencies in accordance with the decision taken by the`
  line `Standing Committee of the National Board for Wild Life constituted under section 5A of the Wild`
  line `Life (Protection) Act, 1972 (35 of 1972) or the orders of the Supreme Court involving cases of`
  line `diversion of forest land in protected areas shall form the corpus and the income therefrom shall be`
  line `used exclusively for undertaking protection and conservation activities in protected areas of the State`
  line `including facilitating voluntary relocation from such protected areas and in exceptional circumstance,`
  line `a part of the corpus may also be used subject to prior approval of the National Authority;`
  line
  line `(e) ten per cent. of amount realised from the user agencies, which has been credited directly into`
  line `the State Fund in a year shall be transferred to the National Fund to meet expenditure as provided in`
  line `clause (b) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(f) the non-recurring and recurring expenditure for the management of a State Authority including`
  line `the salary and allowances payable to its officers and other employees may be met from a part of the`
  line `interest accrued on the amounts available in the State Fund, in the manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(g) in case of trans-boundary forestry or environmental implication of diversion of forest land for`
  line `non-forest purposes in a particular State, if found expedient and necessary by the National Authority,`
  line `it may, in consultation with the concerned Sate Authorities order that such sum as may be justified for`
  line `reparation of the trans-boundary effects, be transferred to State Fund of such State or States;`
  line
  line `(h) State Authority shall release monies to agencies identified for execution of activities in predetermined instalments as per the annual plan of operation finalised by steering committee of such`
  line `State Authority and executive committee of the National Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (31834)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Accounting procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31834&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The accounting procedure to regulate the manner of crediting the`
  line `monies to the National Fund and State Fund in a year shall be in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (31835)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Constitution of National Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31835&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf, there shall be constituted a National`
  line `Authority to be called the "National Compensatory Afforestation Fund Management and Planning`
  line `Authority".`
  line
  line `(2) The National Authority shall manage and utilise the National Fund for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The National Authority shall consist of a governing body and shall be assisted by an executive`
  line `committee, monitoring group and administrative support mechanism.`
  line
  line `(4) The governing body of the National Authority shall consist of the following, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) Minister for Environment, Forest and Climate Change, Government of India—`
  line `Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(ii) Secretaries of Ministries dealing with Environment, Forest, Climate Change, Finance`
  line `(Expenditure), Rural Development, Land Resources, Agriculture, Panchayati Raj, Tribal`
  line `Development, Science, Technology, Space and Earth Sciences and Chief Executive Officer, National`
  line `Institution for Transforming India Ayog, Government of India—Members, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(iii) Director General of Forests and Special Secretary, Ministry of Environment, Forest and`
  line `Climate Change, Government of India—Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(iv) Additional Director General of Forests (Forest Conservation), Ministry of Environment,`
  line `Forest and Climate Change, Government of India—Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(v) Additional Director General of Forests (Wildlife), Ministry of Environment, Forest and`
  line `Climate Change, Government of India—Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(vi) Mission Director, National Mission for a Green India, Ministry of Environment, Forest and`
  line `Climate Change, Government of India—Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(vii) Financial Adviser, Ministry of Environment, Forest and Climate Change, Government of`
  line `India—Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(viii) five Principal Chief Conservator of Forests, not more than one from each of the ten regions,`
  line `to be nominated by the Ministry of Environment, Forest and Climate Change, Government of India`
  line `on rotation basis for a period of two years, at a time—Members, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(ix) Inspector General of Forests (Forest Conservation), Ministry of Environment, Forest and`
  line `Climate Change, Government of India—Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(x) five experts, one each from environmentalists, conservationists, scientists, economists, and`
  line `social scientists appointed by the Central Government for a period of two years subject to not more`
  line `than two consecutive terms—Members.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may appoint an officer of the rank of an Additional Director General of`
  line `Forests as the Chief Executive Officer of the National Authority who shall be the Member—`
  line `Secretary of the governing body and the executive committee of the National Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (31836)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Executive committee and monitoring group of National Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31836&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The governing body`
  line `of the National Authority shall, in performance of its functions and powers under the Act, be assisted by`
  line `the executive committee and the monitoring group.`
  line
  line `(2) The executive committee of the National Authority shall consist of the following, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) Director General of Forests and Special Secretary, Ministry of Environment, Forest and`
  line `Climate Change, Government of India—Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(ii) Additional Director General of Forests (Forest Conservation), Ministry of Environment,`
  line `Forest and Climate Change, Government of India—Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(iii) Additional Director General of Forests (Wildlife), Ministry of Environment, Forest and`
  line `Climate Change, Government of India—Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(iv) Mission Director, National Mission for a Green India, Ministry of Environment, Forest and`
  line `Climate Change, Government of India—Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(v) Financial Adviser, Ministry of Environment, Forest and Climate Change, Government of`
  line `India—Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(vi) Head of all regional offices of the Ministry of Environment, Forest and Climate Change,`
  line `Government of India—Members, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(vii) Inspector General of Forests (Forest Conservation), Ministry of Environment, Forest and`
  line `Climate Change, Government of India—Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(viii) a professional ecologist, not being from the Central Government, to be appointed by the`
  line `Central Government— Member;`
  line
  line `(ix) three experts, one each in the fields of forestry, tribal development, forest economy`
  line `development, not being from the Central Government, to be appointed by the Central Government—`
  line Members;
  line
  line `(x) Chief Executive Officer of the National Authority—Member-Secretary.`
  line
  line `(3) The monitoring group shall consist of six experts in the field of environment, economics, wildlife,`
  line `forest, remote sensing and geographical information system and social sector and the Director General,`
  line `Forest Survey of India, Ministry of Environment, Forest and Climate Change, Government of India.`
  line
  line `(4) The following officers shall be appointed by the National Authority for a period not exceeding`
  line `five years, to assist the executive committee in performance of its functions and powers under the Act,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) Joint Chief Executive Officer of the rank of Inspector General of Forests;`
  line
  line `(ii) Financial Advisor and Chief Accounts Officer of the rank of Director in the Government of`
  line `India; and`
  line
  line `(iii) Deputy Chief Executive Officers of the rank of Deputy Inspector General of Forests.`
  line
  line `(5) The governing body of the National Authority may with the prior concurrence of the Central`
  line `Government create posts in the National Authority at the level of Assistant Inspector General of Forests`
  line `and other officials to assist the executive committee and monitoring group in performance of its functions`
  line `under the Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (31837)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Constitution of State Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31837&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf, there shall be constituted a State`
  line `Authority to be called the "State Compensatory Afforestation Fund Management and Planning Authority"`
  line `in each State.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, if so desires, appoint different dates for constitution of State`
  line `Authority in each of the States.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Authority constituted in a State shall be responsible for the management of the State`
  line `Fund of such State and its utilisation for the purposes of the Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Authority shall consist of a governing body and shall be assisted by a steering`
  line `committee and an executive committee.`
  line
  line `(5) The governing body of a State Authority shall consist of the following, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) Chief Minister of the State and in case of a Union territory having no legislature, the`
  line `Lieutenant Governor or the Administrator, as the case may be—Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(ii) Minister of Forests—Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(iii) Chief Secretary—Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(iv) Principal Secretaries of the Departments dealing with Environment, Finance, Planning, Rural`
  line `Development, Revenue, Agriculture, Tribal Development, Panchayati Raj, Science and`
  line `Technology—Members, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(v) Principal Chief Conservator of Forests (Head of Forest Force)-Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(vi) Chief Wildlife Warden—Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(6) Principal Secretary in-charge of the Forest Department in a State shall be Member Secretary of the`
  line `State Authority in such State.`
  line
  line `(7) The State Government shall appoint an officer of the rank not below the rank of a Chief`
  line `Conservator of Forests as the Chief Executive Officer of the State Authority who shall be the MemberSecretary of the steering committee and the executive committee of the State Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (31838)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Steering committee and executive committee of State Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31838&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The governing body of`
  line `the State Authority shall, in performance of its functions and powers under the Act, be assisted by the`
  line `steering committee and the executive committee.`
  line
  line `(2) The steering committee of a State Authority shall consist of the following, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) Chief Secretary—Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(ii) Principal Secretaries of the Departments dealing with Forests, Environment, Finance,`
  line `Planning, Rural Development, Revenue, Agriculture, Tribal Development, Panchayati Raj, Science`
  line `and Technology—Members, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(iii) Principal Chief Conservator of Forests (Head of Forest Force)—Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(iv) Chief Wildlife Warden—Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(v) Nodal Officer, the Forest (Conservation) Act, 1980 (69 of 1980) Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(vi) Head of the concerned regional office of the Ministry of Environment, Forest and Climate`
  line `Change—Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(vii) Nodal Officer, State Forest Development Agency—Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(viii) an expert on tribal matters or a representative of tribal communities to be appointed by the`
  line `State Government—Member;`
  line
  line `(ix) Chief Executive Officer, State Authority—Member-Secretary.`
  line
  line `(3) The executive committee of a State Authority shall consist of the following, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) Principal Chief Conservator of Forests (Head of Forest Force) —Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(ii) Chief Wildlife Warden—Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(iii) an officer not below the rank of a Chief Conservator of Forests dealing with forest and`
  line `wildlife related schemes—Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(iv) an officer not below the rank of a Chief Conservator of Forests dealing with forestry`
  line `research—Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(v) Nodal Officer, State Forest Development Agency—Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(vi) a representative each of the Departments dealing with Environment, Finance, Planning, Rural`
  line `Development, Revenue, Agriculture, Tribal Development, Panchayati Raj, Science and`
  line `Technology—Members, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(vii) Financial Controller or Financial Adviser, to be nominated by the Finance`
  line `Department—Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(viii) two eminent non-government organisations to be appointed by the State Government—`
  line Members;
  line
  line `(ix) two representatives of district level Panchayati Raj Institutions to be appointed by the State`
  line Government—Members;
  line
  line `(x) an expert on tribal matters or a representative of tribal community to be appointed by the State`
  line Government—Member;
  line
  line `(xi) Chief Executive Officer, State Authority—Member-Secretary.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Authority may appoint the following officers for a period not exceeding five years, to`
  line `assist the steering committee and executive committee in performance of its functions under the Act,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) Joint Chief Executive Officer of the rank not below the rank of a Conservator of Forests;`
  line
  line `(ii) Financial Advisor and Chief Accounts Officer of the rank not below the rank of a Deputy`
  line `Secretary in the State Government;`
  line
  line `(iii) Deputy Chief Executive Officer of the rank not below the rank of a Deputy Conservator of`
  line Forests.
  line
  line `(5) The governing body of the State Authority may with the prior concurrence of the State`
  line `Government create posts in the State Authority at the level of Assistant Conservator of Forests and other`
  line `officials to assist the steering committee and executive committee in performance of its functions under`
  line `the Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (31839)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Term of office and conditions of service of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31839&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act,`
  line `the terms of office and other conditions of the service of the members of the National Authority,`
  line `executive committee, monitoring group, Chief Executive Officer and officials appointed by the National`
  line `Authority, members of State Authority, steering committee and executive committee of each State`
  line `Authority shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (31840)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title Disqualifications.
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31840&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `A person shall be disqualified for being appointed as a member of the`
  line `National Authority, executive committee of the National Authority, a State Authority, steering committee`
  line `and executive committee of a State Authority, monitoring group, if he—`
  line
  line `(i) has been convicted and sentenced to imprisonment for an offence which, in the opinion of the`
  line `Central Government, involves moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(ii) is an undischarged insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(iii) is of unsound mind and stands so declared by the competent court; or`
  line
  line `(iv) has been removed or dismissed from the service of the Government or organisation or`
  line `undertaking owned by the Government; or`
  line
  line `(v) has, in the opinion of the Central Government, such financial or other interest in the National`
  line `Authority or the concerned State Authority as is likely to affect the duties discharged by him of his`
  line `function as a member.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (31841)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Powers and functions of National Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31841&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The governing body of the National`
  line `Authority shall—`
  line
  line `(i) formulate broad policy framework for functioning of the National Authority and State`
  line `Authorities as may be notified by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) approve the annual report and audited accounts of the National Authority;`
  line
  line `(iii) review reports on decision taken by executive committee and monitoring group of the`
  line `National Authority including investment decisions;`
  line
  line `(iv) approve the proposal for the schemes specified in sub-clause (iii) of clause (b) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(v) approve the proposals for creation of posts in the National Authority, subject to prior`
  line `permission of the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(vi) provide a mechanism to State Authorities to resolve issues of inter-State or Centre-State`
  line character;
  line
  line `(vii) formulate such procedures for delegation of financial and administrative powers to the`
  line `National Authority and State Authorities as may be notified by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The governing body of the National Authority shall meet at least once in six months.`
  line
  line `(3) The governing body and executive committee of the National Authority and the monitoring group`
  line `of the National Authority shall meet at such places and shall observe such rules and procedures in regard`
  line `to transaction of business at its meeting, including the quorum thereat, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (31842)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Powers and functions of executive committee of National Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31842&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The executive`
  line `committee of the National Authority shall—`
  line
  line `(i) approve within three months from the date of receipt, annual plan of operations of State`
  line `Authorities, with such amendments as it deems fit and proper;`
  line
  line `(ii) formulate proposals for schemes specified in sub-clause (iii) of clause (b) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(iii) execute schemes specified in sub-clause (iii) of clause (b) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(iv) deploy staff on contract or on deputation basis to the posts in the National Authority;`
  line
  line `(v) formulate proposals for creation of posts in the National Authority at the level of Assistant`
  line `Inspector General of Forests and other officers;`
  line
  line `(vi) invest surplus amounts available in the National Fund;`
  line
  line `(vii) execute other day-to-day work in respect of receipt of amounts in the National Fund;`
  line
  line `(viii) maintain books of account and such other records;`
  line
  line `(ix) facilitate scientific, technological and other assistance that may be required by State`
  line Authorities;
  line
  line `(x) present its decisions to the governing body of the National Authority for information;`
  line
  line `(xi) maintain and update a public information system on the National Authority and present all`
  line `information on its transaction in the public domain;`
  line
  line `(xii) undertake any other work as may be assigned by the governing body of the National`
  line `Authority or the Central Government, from time to time.`
  line
  line `(2) The executive committee of the National Authority shall meet at least once in every three months.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (31843)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Functions of monitoring group.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31843&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The monitoring group shall---`
  line
  line `(i) evolve independent system for concurrent monitoring and evaluation of the works`
  line `implemented in the States and Union territories utilising the funds released by the National`
  line `Authority and State Authorities to ensure effective and proper utilisation of funds by utilising the`
  line `services of the regional offices, of the Central Government in the Ministry of Environment, Forest`
  line `and Climate Change:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may also undertake third party monitoring and evaluation`
  line `of the works implemented in the States and Union territories utilising the funds released by the`
  line `National Authority and State Authorities through individual and institutional experts including`
  line `remote sensing agencies;`
  line
  line `(ii) inspect and undertake financial audit of works executed by utilising the funds released by the`
  line `National Authority and State Authorities in the State and Union territories;`
  line
  line `(iii) devise measures for transparency and accountability.`
  line
  line `(2) The monitoring group shall meet at least once in three months.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (31844)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Powers and functions of State Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31844&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The governing body of a State Authority shall—`
  line
  line `(i) lay down the broad policy framework for the functioning of such State Authority within the`
  line `overall framework notified by the Central Government on the recommendations of the National`
  line Authority;
  line
  line `(ii) review the working of the State Authority from time to time.`
  line
  line `(2) The governing body of a State Authority shall meet at least once in six months.`
  line
  line `(3) The governing body, steering committee and executive committee of a State Authority shall meet`
  line `at such places and shall observe such rules and procedures in regards to transaction of business at its`
  line `meeting, including the quorum thereat, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (31845)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Powers and functions of steering committee of State Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31845&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The steering committee`
  line `of a State Authority shall—`
  line
  line `(i) scrutinise and approve with such amendments as it may deems fit and proper the annual plan`
  line `of operations prepared by the executive committee of such State Authority and send the same to the`
  line `executive committee of the National Authority for final approval;`
  line
  line `(ii) monitor the progress of the utilisation of funds released from the State Fund;`
  line
  line `(iii) review reports on decision taken by executive committee including investment decisions;`
  line
  line `(iv) approve, subject to prior concurrence of the State Government, proposals formulated by the`
  line `executive committee for creation of posts in the State Authority;`
  line
  line `(v) approve annual report of the State Authority and send the same to the State Government to lay`
  line `it, each year, in each House of the State Legislature;`
  line
  line `(vi) ensure inter-departmental coordination.`
  line
  line `(2) The steering committee of a State Authority shall meet at least once in every three months.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (31846)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Functions and powers of executive committee of State Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31846&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The executive`
  line `committee of a State Authority shall—`
  line
  line `(i) formulate and submit annual plan of operations to the steering committee of the State`
  line `Authority for its concurrence;`
  line
  line `(ii) undertake qualitative and quantitative supervision, monitoring and evaluation of the works`
  line `being implemented from amounts available in the State Fund;`
  line
  line `(iii) invest surplus amounts available in the State Fund of such State;`
  line
  line `(iv) maintain books of account and other records;`
  line
  line `(v) submit reports to the steering committee of the State Authority;`
  line
  line `(vi) prepare annual report of the State Authority;`
  line
  line `(vii) deploy staff on contractual basis or on deputation to the posts in the State Authority;`
  line
  line `(viii) formulate proposals for creation of posts in the State Authority;`
  line
  line `(ix) be responsible for delegation of financial or administrative powers;`
  line
  line `(x) be responsible for other day-to-day working in respect of the State Authority;`
  line
  line `(xi) maintain and update public information system on the State Authority and present all`
  line `information on its transaction in the public domain;`
  line
  line `(xii) undertake any other work as may be assigned by the governing body or steering committee`
  line `of the State Authority or the State Government, from time to time.`
  line
  line `(2) The executive committee of a State Authority shall meet at least once in every three months.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (31847)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Budget of National Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31847&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Authority shall prepare its budget for the next`
  line `financial year, showing the estimated receipts and expenditure of the National Authority and forward the`
  line `same to the Central Government, in such form and at such time in each financial year as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) The National Authority, shall adopt financial regulation and procedures, in particular the`
  line `procedure for drawing up and implementing the budget of the National Authority as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (31848)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Investment of funds by National Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31848&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The National Authority may invest its funds,`
  line `including any reserve fund, in the securities of the Central Government and in scheduled banks in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the grants received from the Central Government shall not be invested and shall be`
  line `utilised for the purposes and in the manner attached to it.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (31849)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Accounts and audit of National Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31849&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Authority shall maintain proper`
  line `accounts and other relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be`
  line `prescribed in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the National Authority shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General`
  line `of India at such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with`
  line `such audit shall be payable by the National Authority to the Comptroller and Auditor-General.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General and any other person appointed by him in connection with`
  line `the audit of the accounts of the National Authority shall have the same right and privileges and authority`
  line `in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General generally has in connection with`
  line `the audit of the Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of`
  line `books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect the office of the`
  line `National Authority.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the National Authority as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General or`
  line `any other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon, shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government by the National Authority.`
  line
  line `(5) The Comptroller and Auditor-General shall, within a period of six months from the date of`
  line `commencement of the Act, audit the accounts of the all monies collected by the State Governments and`
  line `Union territory Administrations, which has been placed under the ad hoc Authority and deposited in the`
  line `nationalised banks and submit the report to the Central Government under this section.`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government shall have the power to conduct the special audit or performance audit of`
  line `the National Fund and of the National Authority through the Comptroller and Auditor- General.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (31850)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Annual report of National Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31850&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Authority shall prepare, its annual`
  line `report, giving a full account of its activities during the previous financial year and forward a copy thereof`
  line `to the Central Government, in such form and at such time, for each financial year, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The annual report shall, inter alia, provide for—`
  line
  line `(i) the summary of monitoring and evaluation of activities undertaken from amounts released`
  line `from the National Fund and State Funds during the year;`
  line
  line `(ii) the summary of specific schemes specified in sub-clause (iii) of clause (b) of section 5`
  line `executed during the year;`
  line
  line `(iii) the amount of money received and expended.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (31851)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Annual report and audit report of National Authority to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31851&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall cause the annual report and audit report together with a`
  line `memorandum of action taken on the recommendations contained therein to be laid as soon as may be after`
  line `the reports are received before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (31852)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Budget of State Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31852&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Each State Authority shall prepare its budget for the next`
  line `financial year, showing the estimated receipts and expenditure of the State Authority and forward the`
  line `same to the State Government, in such form and at such time, in each financial year, as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) Each State Authority shall adopt financial regulation and procedures, in particular the procedure`
  line `for drawing up and implementing the budget of the State Authority as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (31853)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Investment of funds by State Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31853&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `State Authority may invest funds available in the`
  line `State Fund of such State in the securities of the Central Government and in scheduled banks in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the grants received from the State Government shall not be invested and shall be`
  line `utilised for the purpose and in the manner prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (31854)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Accounts and audit of State Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31854&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) Each State Authority shall maintain proper`
  line `accounts and other relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be`
  line `prescribed in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of each State Authority shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General at`
  line `such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit`
  line `shall be payable by the State Authority to the Comptroller and Auditor-General.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General and any other person appointed by him in connection with`
  line `the audit of the accounts of the State Authority shall have the same right and privileges and authority in`
  line `connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General generally has in connection with the`
  line `audit of the Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of`
  line `books, accounts, connected vouchers, other documents and papers and to inspect the office of the State`
  line Authority.
  line
  line `(4) The Accounts of the State Authority as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon, shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the State Government by the State Authority.`
  line
  line `(5) The Comptroller and Auditor-General shall, within a period of six months from the date of`
  line `commencement of the Act, audit the accounts of all the monies which have been transferred by the ad`
  line `hoc Authority to the State Compensatory Afforestation Fund Management and Planning Authorities`
  line `constituted in the States in compliance of guidelines dated the 2nd July, 2009 and submit the report to the`
  line `State Government under this section.`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government and the State Government concerned shall have the power to conduct the`
  line `special audit or performance audit of the State Fund and of the State Authority through the Comptroller`
  line `and Auditor-General.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (31855)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Annual report of State Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31855&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Each State Authority shall prepare its annual report,`
  line `giving a full account of its activities during the previous financial year and forward a copy thereof to the`
  line `concerned State Government, in such form and at such time, for each financial year, as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) The annual report of a State Authority shall, inter alia, provide for—`
  line
  line `(i) the number and location of each reforestation, afforestation and conservation activity subject`
  line `to the requirement of this section;`
  line
  line `(ii) the amount and location of lands in hectares, cleared, conserved and planted in connection`
  line `with the activity; and`
  line
  line `(iii) the amount of afforestation money collected and expended.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (31856)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Annual report and audit report of State Authority to be laid before State Legislature.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31856&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The State Government shall cause the annual report and the audit report together with a memorandum of`
  line `action taken on the recommendations contained therein to be laid as soon as may be after the reports are`
  line `received before each House of the State Legislature:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of a Union territory having no legislature, the Central Government shall cause`
  line `the annual report and the audit report together with a memorandum of action taken on the`
  line `recommendations contained therein to be laid as soon as may be after the reports are received before each`
  line `House of the Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (31857)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31857&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government in consultation with the State Governments`
  line `may, after previous publication, make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the management of the National Fund by the National Authority under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the management of State Fund by the State Authorities under sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of using the money for purposes specified in clause (b) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner of utilising the money for purposes specified in clause (c) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner of payment of the salary and allowances payable to the officers and other`
  line `employees of the State Authority under clause (f) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(f) the accounting procedure regulating the manner of crediting the monies to the National Fund`
  line `and State Funds under section 7;`
  line
  line `(g) the terms of office and other conditions of the service of the members of the National`
  line `Authority, executive committee, monitoring group, Chief Executive Officer and officials appointed`
  line `by the National Authority, members of State Authority, steering committee and executive committee`
  line `of each State Authority under section 12;`
  line
  line `(h) the rules and procedures in respect of the transaction of business of the governing body and`
  line `executive committee of the National Authority and monitoring group of the National Authority and`
  line `the place of meeting, including the quorum under sub-section (3) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(i) the rules and procedures in respect of the transaction of business of the governing body,`
  line `steering committee and executive committee of a State Authority and the place of meeting, including`
  line `the quorum under sub-section (3) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(j) the preparation of the budget of the National Authority under sub-section (1) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(k) the financial regulation and procedures, in particular the procedure for drawing up and`
  line `implementing the budget of the National Authority under sub-section (2) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(l) the investment of the funds of the National Authority under section 21;`
  line
  line `(m) the maintenance of the accounts and other relevant records and preparation of an annual`
  line `statement of accounts by the National Authority under sub-section (1) of section 22;`
  line
  line `(n) the preparation of the annual report by the National Authority under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 23;`
  line
  line `(o) the preparation of the budget of the State Authority under sub-section (1) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(p) the financial regulation and procedures, in particular the procedure for drawing up and`
  line `implementing the budget of the State Authorities under sub-section (2) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(q) the investment of funds by the State Authorities under section 26;`
  line
  line `(r) the maintenance of the accounts and other relevant records and preparation of annual`
  line `statement of accounts by each State Authority under sub-section (1) of section 27;`
  line
  line `(s) the preparation of the annual report by the State Authorities under sub-section (1) of section`
  line `28; and`
  line
  line `(t) any other matter which is required to be, or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall, thereafter have effect`
  line `only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification`
  line `or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (31858)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Transfer of assets, liabilities, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31858&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the date of constitution of the National`
  line Authority—
  line
  line `(i) all the assets and liabilities of the ad hoc Authority shall stand transferred to, and vested in, the`
  line `National Authority;`
  line
  line `Explanation.—The assets of the ad hoc Authority shall be deemed to include all rights and`
  line `powers, all properties, whether movable or immovable, including in particular, cash balances,`
  line `deposits, and all other interests and rights in, or arising of, such properties as may be in the possession`
  line `of the ad hoc Authority and all books of account and other documents relating to the same, and`
  line `liabilities shall include all debts, liabilities and obligations of whatever kind;`
  line
  line `(ii) without prejudice to the provisions of clause (i), all debts, obligations and liabilities incurred,`
  line `all contracts entered into and all matters and things engaged to be done by, with or for the ad hoc`
  line `Authority immediately before constitution of the National Authority, for or in connection with the`
  line `purpose of the ad hoc Authority, shall be deemed to have been incurred, entered into or engaged to be`
  line `done by, with or for, the National Authority;`
  line
  line `(iii) all sums of money due to the ad hoc Authority immediately before constitution of the`
  line `National Authority shall be due to the National Authority;`
  line
  line `(iv) all suits and legal proceedings instituted or which could have been instituted by or against the`
  line `ad hoc Authority may be continued or may be instituted by or against the National Compensatory`
  line Authority.
  line
  line `(2) On and from the date of constitution of a State Authority—`
  line
  line `(i) all the assets and liabilities of the State Compensatory Afforestation Fund Management and`
  line `Planning Authority constituted in such State in compliance of guidelines dated the 2nd July, 2009`
  line `shall stand transferred to, and vested in, the State Authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—The assets of the State Compensatory Afforestation Fund Management and`
  line `Planning Authority constituted in such State in compliance of guidelines dated the 2nd July, 2009`
  line `shall be deemed to include all rights and powers, all properties, whether movable or immovable,`
  line `including in particular, cash balances, deposits, and all other interests and rights in, or arising of, such`
  line `properties as may be in the possession of the State Compensatory Afforestation Fund Management`
  line `and Planning Authority constituted in such State in compliance of guidelines dated the 2nd July, 2009`
  line `and all books of account and other documents relating to the same, and liabilities shall include all`
  line `debts, liabilities and obligations of whatever kind;`
  line
  line `(ii) without prejudice to the provisions of clause (i), all debts, obligations and liabilities incurred,`
  line `all contracts entered into and all matters and things engaged to be done by, with or for the State`
  line `Compensatory Afforestation Fund Management and Planning Authority constituted in such State in`
  line `compliance of guidelines dated the 2nd July, 2009 before this Act came into force, for or in`
  line `connection with the purpose of the State Compensatory Afforestation Fund Management and`
  line `Planning Authority constituted in such State in compliance of guidelines dated the 2nd July, 2009,`
  line `shall be deemed to have been incurred, entered into or engaged to be done by, with or for, the State`
  line Authority;
  line
  line `(iii) all sums of money due to the State Compensatory Afforestation Fund Management and`
  line `Planning Authority constituted in such State in compliance of guidelines dated the 2nd July, 2009`
  line `before constitution of the State Authority shall be due to the State Authority;`
  line
  line `(iv) all suits and legal proceedings instituted or which could have been instituted by or against the`
  line `State Compensatory Afforestation Fund Management and Planning Authority constituted in such`
  line `State in compliance of guidelines dated the 2nd July, 2009 may be continued or may be instituted by`
  line `or against the State Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (31859)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title Validation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31859&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any judgment, decree or order of any`
  line `court, the amount credited to the National Fund shall be deemed to be credited and shall always be`
  line `deemed to have been credited to the public account of India within the meaning of articles 266 and 283 of`
  line `the Constitution, and it shall be regulated by law made by Parliament in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any judgment or order of any court, all the monies`
  line `collected by the State Governments and the Union territory Administrations which has been placed under`
  line `the ad hoc Authority and deposited in the nationalised banks and the interest accrued thereon shall stand`
  line `transferred to the National Fund.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any judgment or any order of any court, the amount`
  line `credited to the State Fund shall be deemed to be credited and shall always be deemed to have been`
  line `credited to the public account of the State within the meaning of articles 266 and 283 of the Constitution,`
  line `and it shall be regulated by law made by the State Legislature in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (31860)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204&sectionId=31860&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00012_201638_1517807328204
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, if it`
  line `finds necessary or expedient in the public interest, issue such policy directives to the National Authority`
  line `or any State Authority, in writing and such policy directives shall be binding upon the National Authority`
  line `or the State Authority, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government, whether a question is one of policy or not, shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
